name: jim taylor (jiMTV)
text:
Becca's classes have become a routine part of my life.  Her approach to yoga is encouraging, supportive and at times challenging.

Practice Works is also a great venue. What they have done to this once vacant building is impressive.  There's a lot more than yoga going on here.  I encourage you to check it out.

resp.text: Thanks so much for the positive feedback Jim! We are really glad to have you as part of our community.

name: Riann Nova
text: Quiet, open, clean feeling work flex space

name: Eva Almeshal
text: The organization I work with has hosted several team meetings at Practice Works over the last few months. The staff is incredibly helpful and friendly, and they always go out of their way to accommodate us and make sure that we can safely socially distance while meeting in-person. Since our team is remote, they also help make sure that our out-of-state attendees are able to virtually join us on Zoom without any audio/visual issues. It's always a pleasure coming to PW - from the friendly faces to the wonderful overall atmosphere/ambiance. This will continue to be our go-to spot for future meetings! Highly recommend!

resp.text: Thank you Eva for the kind words. We are honored to serve as the "home" for Coach Safely. We are looking forward too hosting your team again soon.

name: Hamid Al-Dlaigan
text: I booked Practice Works on short notice for an event of 25 people and they are absolutely phenomenal! Our team enjoyed their lobby space and the decor of their rented spaces are ideal for the look and feel we wanted for our event. The team was easy to work with and checked on us throughout the day. I can't say enough about how great this place is and how excellent they are to work with. If you are considering them I highly recommend using them.

resp.text: We were thrilled to be able to accommodate on short notice, Hamid. We love the energy you all brought to the building. We welcome you and your group anytime.

name: Kevin Archer
text: We held an event for 50+ people and the setting was perfect.  The staff was gracious and accommodating and the space was elegant and peaceful.  The event exceeded our expectations.  We will schedule many events here in the future and find ways to support Meredith and Becca.  Practice Works provides a very unique place for corporate trainings, meetings and events to go along with their vast offering of wellness services.  Highly recommended!

resp.text: Thank you, Kevin! We enjoyed hosting you and your clients. What a beautiful night that was indeed.

name: Elizabeth Barbaree-Tasker
text: Practice Works is a lovely and peaceful space. As soon as you walk in the door for a class or a meeting, it's easy to take a deep breath and transition fully into the reason for your visit. That's not an easy feat for a place where a variety of work happens! Whether you're working to achieve personal wellness or professional goals, you can easily do both here in a community of smart and dedicated practitioners. It's a great addition to the city!

resp.text: Thank you for your kind words, Elizabeth. We are happy to be part of your wellness practice!

name: HereNowYoga Teacher Training
text: HereNowYoga has hosted our 200 hour yoga teacher training at Practice Works for the past two years. The space is ideal to support our program and our students. We love the generous amount of common space so that our trainees can spread out and relax when they are there for a long training weekend. This year we have been able to take advantage of technology support at PW to run virtual and live sessions simultaneously and the variety of classrooms gives us the option to break into smaller groups. The space is always clean and beautiful and easy to access.

resp.text: Thank you Kim and Becca for coming back year after year. We so enjoy the love the HNY students bring to our space and community!

name: Darlene L Wilson
text: It's a great space! I like the atmosphere and the ease of use for services. The portal is a great way to schedule appointments and register for the classes that fit within my schedule. I like to be greeted with kindness and care. The staff is amazing. I've taken advantage of several services and all were good to me and for me. I will continue to use the services at Practice-Works. I love the package deals too! Big bang for my bucks...

resp.text: Thank you Darlene! It's always a pleasure to welcome you in to the building. We can't wait to see you again soon.

name: Sommerville B. Johnston
text: Step inside and feel the calm, clean, and healing atmosphere. Practice Works has given me a space for my private practice that supports more than just the external structure (getting out of the house, access to a printer, copier, excellent wifi, and a space to meet clients) but also, more importantly, supports my own wellness. The healthy food options, the calm and beautiful setting, the kindness and support of the staff, and the overall valuing of wellness permeates the environment. I feel better being there! And even during this pandemic, I benefit from being connected to a community of wellness practitioners, having access to a professional space for my Zoom calls and classes, and help thinking through  difficult decisions and aspects of adapting my business to the current community needs. I cannot recommend this space highly enough. Having lived in places like Asheville, NC and Boulder, CO before (both very progressive and health-minded communities), I am grateful to find such a unique offering in Birmingham, and believe that it supports the trajectory of the health and wellness industry for the Magic City.

resp.text: Thank you so much for your kind words, Sommerville! We are lucky to have you as a member!

name: Roy C
text:
The staff, facilities, and classes offered at Practice Works are all top notch.

I have found the meditation classes hosted and guided by Sheri Bagwell to be most beneficial on my path to overall health and well-being. She truly has a vested interest in perpetuating the highest potentials of everyone she encounters.  Highly recommended !!

resp.text: Thanks so much for your positive feedback! We are glad you're part of our Practice Works community!

name: Patti Lovoy
text: Whether attending a heavenly yoga class or having a small strategy meeting, Practice Works takes the stress away and offers soothing, welcoming, spotless accommodations. The environment itself is motivating. What a find in our downtown/southside community.

resp.text: Thank you, Patti. We loved hosting Children's Aid Society for your board committee meeting. We hope you'll make some time for a movement class on the back-end next time around!

name: Valerie Thompson
text: Practice Works is a coworking dream come true for wellness practitioners. I am an LPC and love the clean, warm, inviting coworking space to get my work done. The individual rooms for seeing clients are comfortable and soothing. The front desk staff is helpful and a kind first contact with my clients when they arrive. Co founders Becca and Meredith are innovative, supportive and just great people to know. They work to create community among the practitioners for connection and collaboration. I am so blessed to have found this!

resp.text: Thank you Valerie. We're fortunate to have you in our community!

name: Kirsten Rand
text: Joining the “yard” is hands down one of the best moves I’ve ever made for my business. I had outgrown my home office years ago and needed a professional work environment appropriate for the needs of my growing business. It’s a well designed, flexible, extremely well run and stimulating environment that has catapulted my productivity, energized my team and I, and given me a professional homebase to operate from. I’ve been a member for two months now and, frankly, can’t imagine how I functioned before. Bonus: I’m surrounded by friendly, creative, and entrepreneurial folks, unlimited coffee, and occasional visits from Stacy and Johnny’s two irresistible dogs. A win for my business on all fronts!

name: Eric andrews
text:
The worst service I have ever received from any business.They Lied to us and cost us thousands of dollars. We ended up homeless. The york county south Carolina office is absolutely terrible.  We tried to buy a house using a V.A. loan we were lied to about pre approval for over a month. We broke the lease on our apartment and packed up all our belongings. The day of closing they called us and said they couldn't approve us till September. My wife is a disabled veteran and now 4 months pregnant. Because of the incompetence and blatant dishonesty of mortgage right we were homeless for the 4rth of July. We recently found out from our new loan company that (M.R) never even started the V.A. application process. They knew from day 1 that they wouldn't approve us but still lied to us for a whole month taking our appraisal, and Ernest money. The treatment we received was out right despicable the agents at their South Carolina office. Made us loose a substantial amount of money 1000.00 for the U-haul alone. They will be hearing from our attorney about that.
We will be reporting them to the B.B.B and we are currently in the process of getting this company black listed from the V.A. So no other service members are subjected to these kind of scumbagg business practices..
We are also contacting every news outlet in the following counties. York,lancaster,Chesterfield and Mecklenburg.
Loan company takes advantage of 22 yo pregnant veteran resulting in homelessness on the 4rth of July...what a headline..
